      {
        "id": 2908758,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-06-08T19:57:35.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"161665\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Thank you William - are the trellising wires as high as in her grand crus in the cote de nuits? That would be crazy, as it\u2019s expensive and time consuming to farm this way. Then again, without checking, I assume the price is as high as a grand cru from the cote de nuits, so it might work out.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Yes, they are! All Leroy\u2019s vines are farmed like that, whatever the appellation.</p>\n<p>Wine-Searcher average across all vintages is 652 USD per bottle. So considerably more than many grands crus. The prices have really exploded in the last 18 months for this bottling.</p>",
